text:
The DirectoryScanner's scan-method throws an IllegalStateException if the 
basedir does not exist or is not a directory:

        if (!basedir.exists()) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("basedir does not exist");
        }
        if (!basedir.isDirectory()) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("basedir is not a directory");
        }

Even if complex build's are performed it would be useful to print the name of 
the faulting basedir too. This would ease fixing the build-problem very much.
